The following are major news items in leading South African
newspapers Friday: The Citizen: -- More than a quarter of a million
teachers in South Africa may go on strike next week as negotiations
with the Education Department on retrenchments reached deadlock and a
third major union gave notice of intended strike action. The Star: -- A
former Mozambican official with close ties to former Mozambican
President Samora Machel was among several witnesses who testified
behind closed doors Thursday at a Truth and Reconciliation Commission
hearing into the 1986 air crash that killed Machel. Business Day: --
The South African Chamber of Business business confidence index dropped
1.2 percent in May, following speculation against the Rand, an increase
in the current account deficit and interest rates pressures.
